        <th>Can employers delay the employee�s start date or withdraw a job offer? </th>
        <th>Employers are committed to the employment terms once a job offer was accepted by the employee. However, the employer can negotiate a new start date with its employee. If the individual is no longer required, the employer can dismiss the employee with less than two years� service provided the dismissal is not in connection with discrimination or whistleblowing.</th>
    </tr>
